    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Basically, the strategy is to start first, since there is no problem for you to bid TA LEAST 1 burden. Then you start and play a hobbit companion ( tolman cotton preferably ) from your draw deck and you try to get gandalf in the first hand. Anyway, this deck loses only against intense orc swarm on the first 4 sites and the dwarf-orc discarding cards deck. Anyway your companions ( gandalf, sam, frodo ) have enough strenght to survive till the end and you dont have to hurry because this arcery deck works really well. If you control at least 2 sites at the start of the game, there is a great possibility you will exhaust and kill opponents fellowship and the beauty of it is, that you just play the archers as much as you can so your hand cycles pretty good. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
